---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-13", modifiedDate: "2026-03-19", section: "Business Essentials" };
---

<Layout 
  title="Best Locations for Maine Dispensaries | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="In-depth technical resource for Best Locations for Maine Dispensaries within the Maine cannabis industry. Professional 2026 guidance on licensing, compliance, and strategic market positioning."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1449034446853-66c86144b0ad?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Best Locations for a Dispensary in Maine</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to choose the optimal <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-locations/">location</a> for your Maine cannabis dispensary</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Location is one of the most critical factors in dispensary success. Maine's diverse cities and towns offer different opportunities and challenges. This guide helps you evaluate and choose the best location.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Unlocking Local Potential" type="passion">
      Choosing your location is about finding your place in the fabric of a Maine community. Whether it's a bustling corner in Portland or a cozy storefront in Bangor, your shop will become a landmark for locals and a destination for visitors. It's the moment your business truly finds its "home."
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Location Factors</h2>
      
      <h3>Population & Demographics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Target demographic: age 21+ population within 15-mile radius</li>
        <li>Traffic count: minimum 8,000 vehicles per day on primary road</li>
        <li>Competition analysis: distance from existing licensed dispensaries</li>
        <li>Budget for build-out costs</li>
        <li>Long-term leases (5+ years) recommended</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use/opt-in-communities" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Municipal Opt-In List</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>Market conditions change. Verify current information with local authorities.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  section h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul, ol { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
